# Allowlist, not a blocklist. The repository root holds the test material --
# several MKVs, one of them 21 GB -- and `docker build` uploads the whole
# context to the daemon before it reads the first line of the Dockerfile. A
# forgotten pattern there is not a slow build, it is a build that never starts.
#
# It doubles as a secrets fence: *.env and public/_*.html carry live Emby
# credentials, and nothing here can let them into an image by accident.
*

# Everything the two stages actually read. docker/ belongs here too: the
# Dockerfile is handed to the daemon separately, but the files it COPYs are not,
# so leaving it out fails the build at the COPY line rather than at the top.
!package.json
!package-lock.json
!src
!public
!tools
!docker

# ...minus the parts of public/ that must never ship: vendor/ is rebuilt inside
# the image (40 MB, and a stale local copy would silently win), and _*.html are
# the throwaway token-seeding pages.
public/vendor
public/_*.html
